<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
  <title>Study Abroad Safety for Higher Education -- SafeTrekr</title>
  <meta name="description" content="SafeTrekr assigns a professional safety analyst to review every study abroad program your institution sends -- across 17 dimensions of risk. Government intelligence. Clery Act documentation. Starting at $1,250 per international program.">
  <meta property="og:title" content="Study Abroad Safety Built for Higher Education">
  <meta property="og:description" content="Professional analyst review, government intelligence, and audit-ready documentation for every study abroad program. Complements your existing systems.">
  <meta property="og:image" content="/og/solutions-higher-education.png">
  <meta property="og:type" content="website">
  <link rel="canonical" href="https://safetrekr.com/solutions/higher-education">
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="design-tokens.css">
  <script src="https://cdn.tailwindcss.com"></script>
  <script>
    tailwind.config = {
      theme: {
        extend: {
          colors: {
            background: '#e7ecee',
            foreground: '#061a23',
            card: '#f7f8f8',
            border: '#b8c3c7',
            ring: '#365462',
            muted: { DEFAULT: '#e7ecee', foreground: '#4d5153' },
            primary: {
              50: '#f1f9f4', 100: '#e0f1e6', 200: '#c0e2cd', 300: '#96cfac',
              400: '#6cbc8b', 500: '#4ca46e', 600: '#3f885b', 700: '#33704b',
              800: '#2a5b3d', 900: '#20462f', 950: '#132a1c',
              DEFAULT: '#3f885b', foreground: '#ffffff'
            },
            secondary: {
              DEFAULT: '#123646', foreground: '#f7f8f8',
              light: '#1a4a5e', muted: '#b8c3c7'
            },
            destructive: { DEFAULT: '#c1253e', foreground: '#ffffff' },
            safety: { green: '#22c55e', yellow: '#eab308', red: '#ef4444' },
            dark: {
              surface: 'rgba(255,255,255,0.06)',
              border: 'rgba(255,255,255,0.1)',
              'text-primary': '#f7f8f8',
              'text-secondary': '#b8c3c7',
              accent: '#6cbc8b'
            }
          },
          fontFamily: {
            heading: ['Plus Jakarta Sans', 'system-ui', 'sans-serif'],
            body: ['Inter', 'system-ui', 'sans-serif'],
            mono: ['JetBrains Mono', 'ui-monospace', 'monospace']
          },
          maxWidth: {
            'container': '1280px'
          }
        }
      }
    }
  </script>

  <!-- JSON-LD: BreadcrumbList -->
  <script type="application/ld+json">
  {
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "BreadcrumbList",
    "itemListElement": [
      { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 1, "name": "Home", "item": "https://safetrekr.com/" },
      { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 2, "name": "Solutions", "item": "https://safetrekr.com/solutions" },
      { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 3, "name": "Higher Education", "item": "https://safetrekr.com/solutions/higher-education" }
    ]
  }
  </script>

  <!-- JSON-LD: FAQPage -->
  <script type="application/ld+json">
  {
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "FAQPage",
    "mainEntity": [
      { "@type": "Question", "name": "Does SafeTrekr replace our existing study abroad management system?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "No. SafeTrekr is designed to complement systems like Terra Dotta, Via TRM, StudioAbroad, and custom institutional platforms. Your existing system manages program logistics -- applications, enrollment, housing assignments, academic credit. SafeTrekr adds the independent safety verification layer." }},
      { "@type": "Question", "name": "How does SafeTrekr handle semester-long programs where conditions may change?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Our analyst reviews specifically account for program duration. For semester-long programs, the initial safety binder covers pre-departure conditions. During the program, your faculty leaders and resident directors receive morning and evening safety briefings." }},
      { "@type": "Question", "name": "Can we use SafeTrekr for faculty-led short-term programs?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Yes. Faculty-led programs of any duration benefit from independent safety review. A two-week faculty-led program in Peru carries the same institutional liability as a semester program in London." }},
      { "@type": "Question", "name": "How does this help with Clery Act compliance?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "The Clery Act requires institutions to report crimes and safety incidents at locations controlled by the institution -- including study abroad program sites. SafeTrekr's safety binder documents that your institution conducted a formal safety assessment." }},
      { "@type": "Question", "name": "What about Title IX obligations for programs abroad?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Title IX protections follow students to study abroad program locations. SafeTrekr's safety binder includes emergency protocol documentation, local law enforcement contacts, medical facility locations, and communication infrastructure assessment." }},
      { "@type": "Question", "name": "How quickly do we get the safety binder back?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "3-5 business days from program submission to binder delivery. For programs planned months in advance, this timeline integrates naturally into your pre-departure preparation." }},
      { "@type": "Question", "name": "Can multiple offices access the safety binder?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Yes. You control access to each program's safety binder. It can be shared with your international education office, risk management, general counsel, the provost's office, program faculty, and any other stakeholder." }},
      { "@type": "Question", "name": "How does pricing work for institutions with many programs?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Each program is priced at $1,250 for international programs. Institutions running 15 or more international programs per year qualify for volume pricing." }},
      { "@type": "Question", "name": "Does SafeTrekr cover domestic programs and field trips?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Yes. SafeTrekr reviews domestic programs at $450 per program (day trips) and $750 per program (overnight/multi-day). The same 17-section analysis applies regardless of destination." }},
      { "@type": "Question", "name": "What government data sources does SafeTrekr use?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Our Risk Intelligence Engine pulls data from five government and international agency sources: NOAA, USGS, CDC, GDACS, and ReliefWeb. Each data source is scored using Monte Carlo simulation." }},
      { "@type": "Question", "name": "How does SafeTrekr handle programs with multiple sites?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Our analyst reviews each site independently -- the safety conditions in Barcelona's city center are different from those at a rural archaeological dig. The final binder consolidates all sites into a single comprehensive document." }},
      { "@type": "Question", "name": "Can SafeTrekr handle programs in high-risk regions?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Yes. Our analyst reviews specifically account for infrastructure gaps, political instability, health system limitations, and communication challenges. The safety binder documents the risks, mitigations, and emergency protocols." }}
    ]
  }
  </script>

  <style>
    /* Dot grid background pattern */
    .bg-dot-grid {
      background-image: radial-gradient(circle, var(--color-border) 1px, transparent 1px);
      background-size: 24px 24px;
    }

    /* Sticky in-page nav */
    .page-nav {
      position: sticky;
      top: 72px;
      z-index: 20;
      background: rgba(247, 248, 248, 0.92);
      backdrop-filter: blur(8px);
      -webkit-backdrop-filter: blur(8px);
      border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border);
      transform: translateY(-100%);
      opacity: 0;
      transition: transform 0.3s ease, opacity 0.3s ease;
    }
    .page-nav.visible {
      transform: translateY(0);
      opacity: 1;
    }
    .page-nav-inner {
      overflow-x: auto;
      -ms-overflow-style: none;
      scrollbar-width: none;
      scroll-snap-type: x mandatory;
    }
    .page-nav-inner::-webkit-scrollbar { display: none; }
    .page-nav-link {
      scroll-snap-align: start;
      white-space: nowrap;
      padding: 12px 16px;
      font-size: 14px;
      font-weight: 500;
      color: var(--color-muted-foreground);
      border-bottom: 2px solid transparent;
      transition: color 0.15s ease, border-color 0.15s ease;
    }
    .page-nav-link:hover { color: var(--color-foreground); }
    .page-nav-link.active {
      color: var(--color-primary-700);
      font-weight: 600;
      border-bottom-color: var(--color-primary-500);
    }

    /* Accordion */
    .faq-item { border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border); }
    .faq-trigger {
      display: flex;
      align-items: center;
      justify-content: space-between;
      width: 100%;
      padding: 20px 0;
      background: none;
      border: none;
      cursor: pointer;
      text-align: left;
      font-family: var(--font-heading);
      font-size: clamp(1.0625rem, 1rem + 0.25vw, 1.25rem);
      font-weight: 600;
      line-height: 1.3;
      color: var(--color-foreground);
      gap: 16px;
    }
    .faq-trigger:hover { color: var(--color-primary-700); }
    .faq-trigger svg {
      flex-shrink: 0;
      transition: transform 0.2s ease;
    }
    .faq-trigger[aria-expanded="true"] svg {
      transform: rotate(180deg);
    }
    .faq-content {
      max-height: 0;
      overflow: hidden;
      transition: max-height 0.3s ease;
    }
    .faq-content.open {
      max-height: 800px;
    }
    .faq-content-inner {
      padding-bottom: 20px;
      font-size: clamp(0.9375rem, 0.875rem + 0.15vw, 1rem);
      line-height: 1.65;
      color: var(--color-muted-foreground);
    }

    /* Hero visual composition */
    .hero-visual {
      position: relative;
      width: 100%;
      max-width: 520px;
    }
    .hero-map {
      width: 100%;
      aspect-ratio: 4/3;
      background: linear-gradient(135deg, #d4dce0 0%, #c8d3d8 40%, #bcc8ce 100%);
      border-radius: var(--radius-xl);
      border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
      box-shadow: var(--shadow-lg);
      overflow: hidden;
      position: relative;
    }
    .hero-map svg { width: 100%; height: 100%; }
    .hero-binder-card {
      position: absolute;
      top: -16px;
      right: -16px;
      width: 260px;
      background: white;
      border-radius: var(--radius-xl);
      box-shadow: var(--shadow-xl);
      border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
      padding: 20px;
    }
    .hero-status-badge {
      position: absolute;
      bottom: 24px;
      left: 16px;
    }

    /* Binder preview stack */
    .binder-stack { position: relative; width: 100%; max-width: 360px; padding: 20px; }
    .binder-page {
      background: white;
      border-radius: var(--radius-lg);
      border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
      padding: 24px;
      position: absolute;
      width: 100%;
    }
    .binder-page-back {
      transform: rotate(-2deg) translate(-12px, -16px);
      opacity: 0.7;
      box-shadow: var(--shadow-md);
    }
    .binder-page-mid {
      transform: rotate(-1deg) translate(-6px, -8px);
      opacity: 0.9;
      box-shadow: var(--shadow-lg);
    }
    .binder-page-front {
      position: relative;
      box-shadow: var(--shadow-xl);
    }

    /* Comparison table layout */
    .comparison-row {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
      gap: 24px;
    }
    @media (max-width: 767px) {
      .comparison-row {
        grid-template-columns: 1fr;
        gap: 0;
      }
      .comparison-item + .comparison-item {
        border-top: 1px solid var(--color-border);
        padding-top: 16px;
        margin-top: 16px;
      }
    }

    /* Feature card link arrow hover */
    .feature-card:hover .arrow-icon {
      transform: translateX(4px);
    }
    .arrow-icon {
      transition: transform 0.2s ease;
    }

    /* Site header */
    .site-header {
      position: sticky;
      top: 0;
      z-index: 30;
      background: rgba(247, 248, 248, 0.95);
      backdrop-filter: blur(12px);
      -webkit-backdrop-filter: blur(12px);
      border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    }

    /* Smooth scroll */
    html { scroll-behavior: smooth; }
    @media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce) {
      html { scroll-behavior: auto; }
    }

    /* Fade-up animation */
    @keyframes fadeUp {
      from { opacity: 0; transform: translateY(16px); }
      to { opacity: 1; transform: translateY(0); }
    }
    .animate-fade-up {
      animation: fadeUp 0.6s ease forwards;
    }

    /* Mobile menu */
    .mobile-menu { display: none; }
    .mobile-menu.open { display: flex; }

    /* Pricing card highlight */
    .pricing-card-highlight {
      position: relative;
      border-color: var(--color-primary-400);
      box-shadow: var(--shadow-md), 0 0 0 1px var(--color-primary-200);
    }

    /* Process timeline connector */
    .timeline-connector {
      height: 2px;
      background: var(--color-border);
      flex: 1;
      margin: 0 -8px;
      margin-top: 20px;
    }
    @media (max-width: 1023px) {
      .timeline-connector { display: none; }
    }
  </style>
<script src="https://mcp.figma.com/mcp/html-to-design/capture.js" async></script>
</head>
<body class="font-body" style="background: var(--color-background); color: var(--color-foreground);">

  <!-- Skip navigation -->
  <a href="#main-content" class="sr-only focus:not-sr-only focus:fixed focus:top-4 focus:left-4 focus:z-50 focus:bg-white focus:px-4 focus:py-2 focus:rounded-md focus:shadow-lg focus:text-primary-700 focus:font-semibold focus:outline-none focus:ring-2 focus:ring-ring">
    Skip to main content
  </a>

  <!-- ════════════════════════════════════════════
       SITE HEADER
       ════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
  <header id="site-header" class="fixed top-0 left-0 right-0 z-30 transition-all duration-300" style="height: 80px;">
    <div class="max-w-[1280px] mx-auto px-6 sm:px-8 lg:px-12 h-full flex items-center justify-between">
      <!-- Logo: Horizontal lockup -->
      <a href="/" aria-label="SafeTrekr home" class="flex-shrink-0">
        <svg height="32" viewBox="0 0 180 32" fill="none" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="hidden lg:block" aria-hidden="true">
          <path d="M16 1L3 8v10c0 7.2 5.5 13.9 13 15.9 7.5-2 13-8.7 13-15.9V8L16 1z" fill="none" stroke="#123646" stroke-width="2" stroke-linejoin="round"/>
          <path d="M10 14l4 4 8-8" stroke="#3f885b" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/>
          <text x="40" y="22" font-family="Plus Jakarta Sans, system-ui, sans-serif" font-weight="700" font-size="18" fill="#123646">SafeTrekr</text>
        </svg>
        <svg height="28" viewBox="0 0 180 32" fill="none" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="lg:hidden" aria-hidden="true">
          <path d="M16 1L3 8v10c0 7.2 5.5 13.9 13 15.9 7.5-2 13-8.7 13-15.9V8L16 1z" fill="none" stroke="#123646" stroke-width="2" stroke-linejoin="round"/>
          <path d="M10 14l4 4 8-8" stroke="#3f885b" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/>
          <text x="40" y="22" font-family="Plus Jakarta Sans, system-ui, sans-serif" font-weight="700" font-size="18" fill="#123646">SafeTrekr</text>
        </svg>
      </a>

      <!-- Desktop Nav -->
      <nav aria-label="Main navigation" class="hidden lg:flex items-center gap-8">
        <a href="/platform" class="text-base font-medium text-foreground/70 hover:text-foreground transition-colors duration-150 flex items-center gap-1" style="font-family: var(--font-body);">
          Platform
          <svg class="w-4 h-4 opacity-50" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7"/></svg>
        </a>
        <a href="/solutions" class="text-base font-medium text-foreground/70 hover:text-foreground transition-colors duration-150 flex items-center gap-1" style="font-family: var(--font-body);">
          Solutions
          <svg class="w-4 h-4 opacity-50" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7"/></svg>
        </a>
        <a href="/how-it-works" class="text-base font-medium text-foreground/70 hover:text-foreground transition-colors duration-150" style="font-family: var(--font-body);">How It Works</a>
        <a href="/pricing" class="text-base font-medium text-foreground/70 hover:text-foreground transition-colors duration-150" style="font-family: var(--font-body);">Pricing</a>
        <a href="/resources" class="text-base font-medium text-foreground/70 hover:text-foreground transition-colors duration-150 flex items-center gap-1" style="font-family: var(--font-body);">
          Resources
          <svg class="w-4 h-4 opacity-50" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7"/></svg>
        </a>
      </nav>

      <!-- Desktop CTAs -->
      <div class="hidden lg:flex items-center gap-4">
        <a href="https://app.safetrekr.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-sm font-semibold transition-colors duration-150 hover:text-foreground" style="font-family: var(--font-heading); color: var(--color-muted-foreground);">Sign In</a>
        <a href="/demo" class="inline-flex items-center justify-center font-semibold rounded-md transition-all duration-150 text-white" style="font-family: var(--font-heading); background: var(--color-primary-600); padding: 10px 20px; font-size: 15px; border-radius: var(--radius-md); text-decoration: none;">Get a Demo</a>
      </div>

      <!-- Mobile Hamburger -->
      <button id="mobile-menu-btn" class="lg:hidden p-2 text-foreground" aria-label="Open navigation menu" aria-expanded="false">
        <svg class="w-6 h-6" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2">
          <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M4 6h16M4 12h16M4 18h16"/>
        </svg>
      </button>
    </div>
  </header>

  <!-- ════════════════════════════════════════════
       IN-PAGE NAVIGATION (Sticky, appears on scroll)
       ════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
  <nav id="page-nav" class="page-nav" aria-label="Page sections">
    <div class="max-w-container mx-auto px-5 sm:px-8 lg:px-12">
      <div class="page-nav-inner flex items-center lg:justify-center gap-0">
        <a href="#challenge" class="page-nav-link" data-section="challenge">The Challenge</a>
        <a href="#how-it-works" class="page-nav-link" data-section="how-it-works">How It Works</a>
        <a href="#sample-binder" class="page-nav-link" data-section="sample-binder">Sample Binder</a>
        <a href="#pricing" class="page-nav-link" data-section="pricing">Pricing</a>
        <a href="#compliance" class="page-nav-link" data-section="compliance">Security</a>
        <a href="#faq" class="page-nav-link" data-section="faq">FAQ</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </nav>

  <!-- ════════════════════════════════════════════
       MAIN CONTENT
       ════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
  <main id="main-content">

    <!-- ──────────────────────────────────────────
         SECTION 1: HERO
         ────────────────────────────────────────── -->
    <section id="hero" aria-label="Hero" style="background: var(--color-background);" class="pt-8 pb-12 sm:pt-12 sm:pb-16 md:pt-16 md:pb-20 lg:pt-20 lg:pb-28 xl:pt-28 xl:pb-36">
      <div class="max-w-container mx-auto px-5 sm:px-8 lg:px-12">

        <!-- Breadcrumb -->
        <nav aria-label="Breadcrumb" class="mb-6 lg:mb-8">
          <ol class="flex items-center gap-2 text-sm" style="color: var(--color-muted-foreground);">
            <li><a href="/" class="hover:underline" style="color: var(--color-primary-700);">Home</a></li>
            <li aria-hidden="true" class="select-none">/</li>
            <li><a href="/solutions" class="hover:underline" style="color: var(--color-primary-700);">Solutions</a></li>
            <li aria-hidden="true" class="select-none">/</li>
            <li aria-current="page" class="font-medium" style="color: var(--color-foreground);">Higher Education</li>
          </ol>
        </nav>

        <div class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-2 gap-12 lg:gap-16 items-center">
          <!-- Text Column -->
          <div>
            <!-- Eyebrow -->
            <div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-5">
              <svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="var(--color-primary-700)" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M22 10v6M2 10l10-5 10 5-10 5z"/><path d="M6 12v5c3 3 9 3 12 0v-5"/></svg>
              <span class="text-eyebrow" style="color: var(--color-primary-700);">STUDY ABROAD SAFETY</span>
            </div>

            <!-- Headline -->
            <h1 class="text-display-xl max-w-[20ch]" style="color: var(--color-foreground);">
              Your Study Abroad Programs Deserve a Safety Analyst
            </h1>

            <!-- Subheadline -->
            <p class="text-body-lg mt-6 max-w-[50ch]" style="color: var(--color-muted-foreground);">
              SafeTrekr brings professional safety review to every study abroad program, faculty-led trip, and international research expedition your institution sends. Government intelligence. 17-section analyst review. Clery Act-ready documentation that complements your existing study abroad systems -- not replaces them.
            </p>

            <!-- CTAs -->
            <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row flex-wrap gap-4 mt-8">
              <a href="/resources/sample-binders/study-abroad" class="btn btn-lg btn-primary">
                <svg width="18" height="18" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M21 15v4a2 2 0 01-2 2H5a2 2 0 01-2-2v-4"/><polyline points="7 10 12 15 17 10"/><line x1="12" y1="15" x2="12" y2="3"/></svg>
                Download Study Abroad Sample Binder
              </a>
              <a href="/demo" class="btn btn-lg btn-secondary">
                Get a Demo
                <svg width="18" height="18" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"><line x1="5" y1="12" x2="19" y2="12"/><polyline points="12 5 19 12 12 19"/></svg>
              </a>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- Visual Column -->
          <div class="flex justify-center lg:justify-end" aria-hidden="true">
            <p class="sr-only">Composed interface showing a study abroad safety binder with map intelligence, analyst review status, and evidence documentation.</p>
            <div class="hero-visual">
              <!-- Map Fragment (Western Europe) -->
              <div class="hero-map">
                <svg viewBox="0 0 480 360" fill="none" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">
                  <!-- Desaturated map background -->
                  <rect width="480" height="360" fill="#d4dce0"/>
                  <!-- Water (Mediterranean) -->
                  <path d="M0 260 Q80 240 160 270 Q240 300 320 260 Q400 220 480 250 V360 H0 Z" fill="#c0cdd3" opacity="0.5"/>
                  <!-- Iberian Peninsula landmass -->
                  <path d="M60 80 Q100 50 180 60 Q240 70 300 55 Q360 40 420 65 Q460 80 480 120 V220 Q440 240 380 230 Q320 220 260 240 Q200 260 140 230 Q80 200 40 180 Q20 160 20 130 Q20 100 60 80Z" fill="#bcc8ce"/>
                  <!-- France/Southern Europe -->
                  <path d="M300 40 Q340 20 400 30 Q440 40 480 60 V120 Q460 100 420 95 Q380 90 340 100 Q300 110 280 90 Q280 60 300 40Z" fill="#b0bec5"/>
                  <!-- Route path: Barcelona - Madrid - Seville -->
                  <path d="M340 130 Q280 145 220 155 Q180 165 140 190" stroke="var(--color-primary-500)" stroke-width="3" stroke-dasharray="8 4" fill="none" opacity="0.8"/>
                  <!-- Waypoint: Barcelona -->
                  <circle cx="340" cy="130" r="8" fill="white" stroke="var(--color-primary-500)" stroke-width="2.5"/>
                  <circle cx="340" cy="130" r="3" fill="var(--color-primary-500)"/>
                  <!-- Waypoint: Madrid -->
                  <circle cx="220" cy="155" r="8" fill="white" stroke="var(--color-primary-500)" stroke-width="2.5"/>
