    <!-- ──────────────────────────────────────────
         SECTION 3: THE CHALLENGE
         ────────────────────────────────────────── -->
    <section id="challenge" aria-labelledby="challenge-heading" style="background: var(--color-background);" class="py-12 sm:py-16 md:py-20 lg:py-24 xl:py-32">
      <div class="max-w-container mx-auto px-5 sm:px-8 lg:px-12">
        <div class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-12 gap-12 lg:gap-16">
          <!-- Left Column: Header + Narrative -->
          <div class="lg:col-span-5">
            <!-- Eyebrow -->
            <div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-5">
              <svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="var(--color-primary-700)" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M10.29 3.86L1.82 18a2 2 0 001.71 3h16.94a2 2 0 001.71-3L13.71 3.86a2 2 0 00-3.42 0z"/><line x1="12" y1="9" x2="12" y2="13"/><line x1="12" y1="17" x2="12.01" y2="17"/></svg>
              <span class="text-eyebrow" style="color: var(--color-primary-700);">THE REALITY TODAY</span>
            </div>

            <!-- Headline -->
            <h2 id="challenge-heading" class="text-display-md max-w-[28ch]" style="color: var(--color-foreground);">
              Study Abroad Safety Cannot Live in a Spreadsheet
            </h2>

            <!-- Body -->
            <p class="text-body-lg mt-6 max-w-prose" style="color: var(--color-muted-foreground);">
              Every year, universities send thousands of students to unfamiliar countries through study abroad programs, faculty-led trips, and international research placements. Most institutions rely on third-party program providers to handle safety -- but when the State Department issues a travel advisory, when a natural disaster strikes, when a student is hospitalized overseas, the institution's name is on the Clery Act report. Not the provider's.
            </p>

            <!-- Closing -->
            <p class="text-body-lg mt-4 max-w-prose font-medium" style="color: var(--color-foreground);">
              Your institution's reputation is not something a third-party provider can protect for you.
            </p>
          </div>

          <!-- Right Column: Status Quo Cards -->
          <div class="lg:col-span-7">
            <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
              <!-- Card 1 -->
              <div class="card card-flat p-6">
                <svg width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="var(--color-muted-foreground)" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true" class="mb-4"><path d="M14 2H6a2 2 0 00-2 2v16a2 2 0 002 2h12a2 2 0 002-2V8z"/><polyline points="14 2 14 8 20 8"/><line x1="16" y1="13" x2="8" y2="13"/><line x1="16" y1="17" x2="8" y2="17"/><polyline points="10 9 9 9 8 9"/></svg>
                <h3 class="text-heading-sm mb-2" style="color: var(--color-foreground);">Third-Party Provider Safety Assessments You Cannot Verify</h3>
                <p class="text-body-sm" style="color: var(--color-muted-foreground);">Program providers conduct their own safety reviews of their own programs. Your international education office receives summaries, not source data. When a parent asks what independent verification your institution performed, the honest answer is usually: we relied on the provider's word.</p>
              </div>

              <!-- Card 2 -->
              <div class="card card-flat p-6">
                <svg width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="var(--color-muted-foreground)" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true" class="mb-4"><path d="M12 22s8-4 8-10V5l-8-3-8 3v7c0 6 8 10 8 10z"/></svg>
                <h3 class="text-heading-sm mb-2" style="color: var(--color-foreground);">Risk Matrices Built from Travel Advisories and Google Searches</h3>
                <p class="text-body-sm" style="color: var(--color-muted-foreground);">Study abroad offices compile safety information from State Department advisories, news articles, and colleague networks. No standardized methodology. No government intelligence beyond what is publicly searchable. No audit trail documenting the assessment process.</p>
              </div>

              <!-- Card 3 -->
              <div class="card card-flat p-6">
                <svg width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="var(--color-muted-foreground)" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true" class="mb-4"><path d="M17 21v-2a4 4 0 00-4-4H5a4 4 0 00-4 4v2"/><circle cx="9" cy="7" r="4"/><path d="M23 21v-2a4 4 0 00-3-3.87"/><path d="M16 3.13a4 4 0 010 7.75"/></svg>
                <h3 class="text-heading-sm mb-2" style="color: var(--color-foreground);">Clery Act Reporting Gaps for Off-Campus International Programs</h3>
                <p class="text-body-sm" style="color: var(--color-muted-foreground);">The Clery Act requires timely reporting of crimes and safety incidents at institution-controlled locations -- including study abroad sites. Many institutions lack the documentation infrastructure to demonstrate they monitored conditions at international program locations before incidents occurred.</p>
              </div>

              <!-- Card 4 -->
              <div class="card card-flat p-6">
                <svg width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="var(--color-muted-foreground)" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true" class="mb-4"><circle cx="12" cy="12" r="10"/><line x1="12" y1="8" x2="12" y2="12"/><line x1="12" y1="16" x2="12.01" y2="16"/></svg>
                <h3 class="text-heading-sm mb-2" style="color: var(--color-foreground);">Title IX Obligations That Do Not Stop at the Border</h3>
                <p class="text-body-sm" style="color: var(--color-muted-foreground);">Title IX protections follow students abroad. If an incident occurs during a faculty-led program in Florence, your institution's response is evaluated by the same standards as an on-campus incident. Without documented safety planning and emergency protocols, the institutional exposure is significant.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>


    <!-- ──────────────────────────────────────────
         SECTION 4: HOW SAFETREKR SOLVES IT
         ────────────────────────────────────────── -->
    <section id="how-it-works" aria-labelledby="solution-heading" class="bg-dot-grid py-12 sm:py-16 md:py-20 lg:py-24 xl:py-32" style="background-color: var(--color-background);">
      <div class="max-w-container mx-auto px-5 sm:px-8 lg:px-12">

        <!-- Section Header (centered) -->
        <div class="text-center mb-12 lg:mb-16">
          <div class="flex items-center justify-center gap-2 mb-5">
            <svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="var(--color-primary-700)" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M12 22s8-4 8-10V5l-8-3-8 3v7c0 6 8 10 8 10z"/></svg>
            <span class="text-eyebrow" style="color: var(--color-primary-700);">HOW SAFETREKR WORKS</span>
          </div>
          <h2 id="solution-heading" class="text-display-md max-w-[28ch] mx-auto" style="color: var(--color-foreground);">
            Professional Safety Review for Every International Program
          </h2>
          <p class="text-body-lg mt-4 max-w-prose mx-auto" style="color: var(--color-muted-foreground);">
            SafeTrekr complements your existing study abroad management systems. We handle the independent safety verification your institution cannot get from a program provider.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Three-Act Process Timeline -->
        <ol class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-8 lg:gap-6 mb-16">
          <!-- Step 1 -->
          <li class="flex flex-col">
            <div class="flex items-start gap-4 lg:flex-col">
              <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-10 h-10 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center font-heading font-semibold text-lg" style="background: var(--color-primary-100); color: var(--color-primary-700);">1</div>
              <div>
                <h3 class="text-heading-md mb-2" style="color: var(--color-foreground);">Intelligence Gathering</h3>
                <p class="text-body-md max-w-[45ch]" style="color: var(--color-muted-foreground);">Before your students arrive in-country, we pull real-time safety data from NOAA, USGS, CDC, ReliefWeb, and GDACS -- the same sources humanitarian agencies use to assess field conditions. Weather patterns at every program location. Seismic risk. Disease advisories. Political stability indicators. Every data point scored, not just collected.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </li>

          <!-- Step 2 -->
          <li class="flex flex-col">
            <div class="flex items-start gap-4 lg:flex-col">
              <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-10 h-10 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center font-heading font-semibold text-lg" style="background: var(--color-primary-100); color: var(--color-primary-700);">2</div>
              <div>
                <h3 class="text-heading-md mb-2" style="color: var(--color-foreground);">Analyst Safety Review</h3>
                <p class="text-body-md max-w-[45ch]" style="color: var(--color-muted-foreground);">A trained safety analyst reviews every detail of your study abroad program across 17 sections -- host institution vetting, housing safety, in-country transportation, emergency medical facilities, evacuation routes, communication infrastructure, mental health resources, and more. Independent of the program provider. Independent of marketing materials.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </li>

          <!-- Step 3 -->
          <li class="flex flex-col">
            <div class="flex items-start gap-4 lg:flex-col">
              <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-10 h-10 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center font-heading font-semibold text-lg" style="background: var(--color-primary-100); color: var(--color-primary-700);">3</div>
              <div>
                <h3 class="text-heading-md mb-2" style="color: var(--color-foreground);">Documented Evidence Binder</h3>
                <p class="text-body-md max-w-[45ch]" style="color: var(--color-muted-foreground);">Your institution receives a complete safety binder -- every review finding, every government data source, every decision documented with tamper-evident audit trails. When a parent asks what safety review was conducted, when the provost needs documentation for a Clery Act filing, when risk management requires evidence of due diligence for an insurance claim -- you hand them the binder.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </li>
        </ol>

        <!-- Feature Cards (2x2) -->
        <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
          <!-- Card 1: Analyst Safety Review -->
          <a href="/platform/analyst-review" class="feature-card card p-6 group block no-underline" style="color: inherit;">
            <svg width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="var(--color-primary-700)" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true" class="mb-4"><path d="M9 11l3 3L22 4"/><path d="M21 12v7a2 2 0 01-2 2H5a2 2 0 01-2-2V5a2 2 0 012-2h11"/></svg>
            <h3 class="text-heading-sm mb-2" style="color: var(--color-foreground);">Every Program Location Reviewed by an Independent Analyst</h3>
            <p class="text-body-sm mb-4" style="color: var(--color-muted-foreground);">Your study abroad office focuses on student success. Our analyst focuses on safety. 17 sections covering host institutions, housing, transportation, emergency contacts, evacuation routes, local hospitals, mental health resources, and more -- independent of what the program provider tells you.</p>
            <span class="text-body-sm font-medium inline-flex items-center gap-1" style="color: var(--color-primary-700);">
              Learn about analyst review
              <svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="arrow-icon"><line x1="5" y1="12" x2="19" y2="12"/><polyline points="12 5 19 12 12 19"/></svg>
            </span>
          </a>

          <!-- Card 2: Risk Intelligence -->
          <a href="/platform/risk-intelligence" class="feature-card card p-6 group block no-underline" style="color: inherit;">
            <svg width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="var(--color-primary-700)" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true" class="mb-4"><path d="M21 10c0 7-9 13-9 13s-9-6-9-13a9 9 0 0118 0z"/><circle cx="12" cy="10" r="3"/></svg>
            <h3 class="text-heading-sm mb-2" style="color: var(--color-foreground);">Government Data on Every Destination Your Students Visit</h3>
            <p class="text-body-sm mb-4" style="color: var(--color-muted-foreground);">Real-time intelligence from 5 government sources -- not a travel advisory summary. NOAA weather data, CDC health advisories, USGS seismic activity, and two international humanitarian agencies. Risk scored with Monte Carlo simulation so you understand probability, not just State Department color codes.</p>
            <span class="text-body-sm font-medium inline-flex items-center gap-1" style="color: var(--color-primary-700);">
              Learn about risk intelligence
              <svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="arrow-icon"><line x1="5" y1="12" x2="19" y2="12"/><polyline points="12 5 19 12 12 19"/></svg>
            </span>
          </a>

          <!-- Card 3: Trip Safety Binder -->
          <a href="/platform/safety-binder" class="feature-card card p-6 group block no-underline" style="color: inherit;">
            <svg width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="var(--color-foreground)" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true" class="mb-4"><path d="M14 2H6a2 2 0 00-2 2v16a2 2 0 002 2h12a2 2 0 002-2V8z"/><polyline points="14 2 14 8 20 8"/><line x1="16" y1="13" x2="8" y2="13"/><line x1="16" y1="17" x2="8" y2="17"/><polyline points="10 9 9 9 8 9"/></svg>
            <h3 class="text-heading-sm mb-2" style="color: var(--color-foreground);">Clery Act-Ready Documentation for Your Institution</h3>
            <p class="text-body-sm mb-4" style="color: var(--color-muted-foreground);">Every finding documented. Every data source cited. Every decision recorded with SHA-256 tamper-evident audit trails. The documentation your risk management office needs for Clery Act compliance, the evidence your general counsel needs for liability defense, and the proof parents need to trust your institution with their student.</p>
            <span class="text-body-sm font-medium inline-flex items-center gap-1" style="color: var(--color-primary-700);">
              Learn about the safety binder
              <svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="arrow-icon"><line x1="5" y1="12" x2="19" y2="12"/><polyline points="12 5 19 12 12 19"/></svg>
            </span>
          </a>

          <!-- Card 4: Mobile Field Operations -->
          <a href="/platform/mobile-app" class="feature-card card p-6 group block no-underline" style="color: inherit;">
            <svg width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="var(--color-safety-green)" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true" class="mb-4"><polyline points="22 12 18 12 15 21 9 3 6 12 2 12"/></svg>
            <h3 class="text-heading-sm mb-2" style="color: var(--color-foreground);">Emergency Protocols and Check-Ins for Every Faculty Leader and Resident Director</h3>
            <p class="text-body-sm mb-4" style="color: var(--color-muted-foreground);">During your program, every faculty leader and resident director gets the SafeTrekr mobile app -- live geofencing, muster check-ins, rally point navigation, SMS broadcast, and morning/evening safety briefings. When a student does not check in, your international education office knows immediately -- not 12 hours later.</p>
            <span class="text-body-sm font-medium inline-flex items-center gap-1" style="color: var(--color-primary-700);">
              Learn about mobile operations
              <svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="arrow-icon"><line x1="5" y1="12" x2="19" y2="12"/><polyline points="12 5 19 12 12 19"/></svg>
            </span>
          </a>
        </div>
